President Obama has nominated Ketanji Brown Jackson to be a member of the U.S. Sentencing Commission. Jackson is currently an attorney at Morrison & Foerster, LLP and has previously worked as an Assistant Federal Public Defender and Assistant Special Counsel to the U.S. Sentencing Commission. She has also served as a law clerk to several judges, including Justice Stephen G. Breyer. Jackson is a graduate of Harvard College and Harvard Law School. President Obama praised her as a top-flight attorney and dedicated public servant, expressing confidence that she will be a strong advocate for justice and fairness on the Sentencing Commission.